The paper focuses on analysing online social networks and their users' behavior, which falls under the category of social media and social networking (cs.SOC). The study also involves monitoring and analysing data, which can be classified under information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper discusses the impact of profile properties on popularity, which can be related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the study involves analysing personal information, which can be related to cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper focuses on a business-oriented social network, which can be classified under social informatics (cs.SI).
